<subSubSection lastPageId="67" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1437,1804,2009]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1804,1829]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Description.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[359,441,1804,1829]" captionStart="FIGURE 43" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1682,1704]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,474,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[151,1436,474,1660]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 43. Petromica (Chaladesma) citrina Muricy, Hajdu, Minervino, Madeira &amp; Peixinho, 2001, a, habitus of RMNH Por. 9990 (scale bar = 1 cm), b – d, SEM images of spicules, b, larger oxeote spicule, b 1, details of b, c, smaller oxeote spicule, c 1, details of c, d, various shapes of desmas." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272994/files/figure.png" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
a) From a (buried) mass rise erect conical, grooved papillae/fistules with frayed endings. Size of basal mass up to 
<date box="[429,465,1840,1865]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">5 x</date>
<quantity box="[472,527,1840,1865]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" unit="cm" value="6.0">6 cm</quantity>
in lateral expansion, height of papillae 
<quantity box="[973,1081,1840,1865]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" unit="cm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 cm</quantity>
. Color in alcohol yellow-white. Surface between the grooves smooth. A few small oscules are present at the base of the papillae. Consistency firm but compressible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1437,1804,2009]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1948,1973]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Skeleton.</emphasis>
Surface skeleton a tangential crust of intercrossing oxeas. Choanosomal skeleton of confusedly arranged oxeas, with vague ascending tracts in the papillae. Loose desmas are concentrated in the basal mass.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,151,645]" box="[199,658,151,176]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,151,176]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Spicules.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[319,403,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 43" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1682,1704]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,474,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[151,1436,474,1660]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 43. Petromica (Chaladesma) citrina Muricy, Hajdu, Minervino, Madeira &amp; Peixinho, 2001, a, habitus of RMNH Por. 9990 (scale bar = 1 cm), b – d, SEM images of spicules, b, larger oxeote spicule, b 1, details of b, c, smaller oxeote spicule, c 1, details of c, d, various shapes of desmas." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272994/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Figs 43</figureCitation>
b–d) Oxeotes, desmas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
Oxeotes (
<figureCitation box="[307,395,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 43" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1682,1704]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,474,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[151,1436,474,1660]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 43. Petromica (Chaladesma) citrina Muricy, Hajdu, Minervino, Madeira &amp; Peixinho, 2001, a, habitus of RMNH Por. 9990 (scale bar = 1 cm), b – d, SEM images of spicules, b, larger oxeote spicule, b 1, details of b, c, smaller oxeote spicule, c 1, details of c, d, various shapes of desmas." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272994/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Figs 43</figureCitation>
b–c), predominantly sharply pointed oxeas, stylote modifications not uncommon, in a large size range but no clear size categories, 721– 
<emphasis box="[644,686,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">949</emphasis>
– 
<date box="[701,797,224,248]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" value="1338-10-09">1338 x 9</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[812,861,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">17.6</emphasis>
–27 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
Desmas (
<figureCitation box="[304,392,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 43" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1682,1704]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,474,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[151,1436,474,1660]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 43. Petromica (Chaladesma) citrina Muricy, Hajdu, Minervino, Madeira &amp; Peixinho, 2001, a, habitus of RMNH Por. 9990 (scale bar = 1 cm), b – d, SEM images of spicules, b, larger oxeote spicule, b 1, details of b, c, smaller oxeote spicule, c 1, details of c, d, various shapes of desmas." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272994/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Figs 43</figureCitation>
d), monocrepid, with irregularly ramose cladi and shorter or longer rhabds, overall cladome size 310– 
<emphasis box="[257,299,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">513</emphasis>
–720 µm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="68" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,505,332,357]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[516,603,332,356]" name="Guyana" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Guyana</collectingCountry>
Shelf, SE 
<collectingCountry box="[733,804,332,357]" name="Brazil" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<quantity box="[818,909,332,357]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" unit="m" value="34.0" valueMax="65.0" valueMin="3.0">3–65 m</quantity>
, encrusting rocks partially buried in the sand (previously down to 
<quantity box="[383,444,367,392]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" unit="m" value="25.0">25 m</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="68" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1424726259" country="Brazil" location="Brazil" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,404,429]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Remarks.</emphasis>
Although this species was described from SE 
<collectingCountry box="[851,919,404,429]" name="Brazil" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and apparently so far restricted to areas S of 22°S, the present specimens share the same habitus and general spiculation and thus appear conspecific, considerably extending the distribution of the species. The oxeas of our specimens have a longer upper length, but overlap in size with the 
<typeStatus box="[433,481,512,536]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">type</typeStatus>
material from 
<collectingCountry box="[657,729,511,536]" name="Brazil" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Brazil</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1424726257" country="Guyana" location="Central West" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Central West" typeStatus="holotype">
A second species of 
<emphasis box="[984,1267,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicName box="[984,1100,513,536]" class="Demospongiae" family="Desmanthidae" genus="Petromica" kingdom="Animalia" order="'lithistida'" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">Petromica</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1117,1259,511,536]" class="Demospongiae" family="Desmanthidae" genus="Chaladesma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bubarida" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">Chaladesma</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
in the 
<collectingRegion isEnumeration="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Central West</collectingRegion>
Atlantic is 
<taxonomicName authority="Van Soest &amp; Zea, 1986" authorityName="Van Soest &amp; Zea" authorityYear="1986" box="[337,865,548,573]" class="Demospongiae" family="Desmanthidae" genus="Petromica" kingdom="Animalia" order="'lithistida'" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ciocalyptoides" subGenus="Chaladesma">
<emphasis box="[337,579,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">P. (C.) ciocalyptoides</emphasis>
(Van Soest &amp; Zea, 1986)
</taxonomicName>
(originally as 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirkpatrick, 1903" authorityName="Kirkpatrick" authorityYear="1903" box="[1029,1155,548,573]" class="Demospongiae" family="Desmanthidae" genus="Monanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bubarida" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1155,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Monanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) differs from the present specimen by having a habitus of smooth conical fistules and possessing smaller oxeas. Assuming that both species are indeed different valid species, the Brazilian species has overall more similarity with the 
<collectingCountry box="[1179,1266,620,644]" name="Guyana" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Guyana</collectingCountry>
material
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
